#!/usr/bin/pseudocode
This is not yet a runnable script

$ sudo apt-get update; apt-get upgrade
$ sudo apt-get install git
$ cd ~
$ git clone git://github.com/AGNUcius/GNUnix.git

$ mv GNUnix/* .
$ mv GNUnix/.* .


This gives you a complete desktop
Maybe try 'slim' or 'lightdm' instead of 'wdm'
Maybe try 'urxvt' or 'aterm' instead of 'xterm'
$ sudo apt-get install xinit xterm icewm big-cursor xlock htop wdm


This gives you a web browser
Maybe try 'firefox' or 'iceweasle' instead
$ sudo apt-get install chromium-browser


The following are tools I must have
$ sudo apt-get install emacs p7zip-full moc gom dhex


$ if (laptop)
$ {
$  sudo apt-get install pm-utils yacpi wicd-curses wireless-regdb crda iw rfkill
$  sudo rfkill list all
$  sudo pm-powersave
$ }


This might fix sound problems
$ sudo add user audio


For the first login (if using wdm), you will need to select "icewm-session" from the "Start WM" button.


See ../README.txt for more info
